article.description: Kayla Tetschlag had 20 points and 10 rebounds Saturday to help Green Bay (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) complete a perfect run through the Horizon League with a 68-48 victory at Detroit.
article.headline: Kayla Tetschlag scores 20 points as Green Bay beats Detroit
article.linkText: Green Bay rolls, finishes 18-0 in Horizon League
article.story:
DETROIT -- Kayla Tetschlag had 20 points and 10 rebounds Saturday to help Green Bay (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) complete a perfect run through the Horizon League with a 68-48 victory at Detroit.

The Phoenix (29-1, 18-0) trailed 40-37 five minutes into the second half but went on an 11-0 run to take the lead for good. Green Bay held the Titans to just four second-half field goals in winning its 20th straight game.

Adrian Ritchie added 15 points, Celeste Hoewisch had 10 and Julie Wojta matched her career-high with eight assists for the Phoenix, who are unbeaten after league play for the second time in the last three seasons.

Britney Murphy scored a career-best 16 points to lead Detroit (12-17, 6-12).
